# my-workplace git identities — copy to "git-identities.conf" and fill in.
# The real file (git-identities.conf) is gitignored: your names/emails stay LOCAL.
#
# One identity per line:  platform|org|Full Name|email
#
#   platform  github | azure | url
#     github   matches https + ssh GitHub remotes for <org>
#     azure    matches dev.azure.com, ssh v3, and <org>.visualstudio.com for <org>
#     url      <org> field is a raw remote-URL glob; use ** as the wildcard
#   org       the organization slug (as it appears in the remote URL), or a
#             raw URL glob when platform is "url"
#
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# The signing KEY is the same for every org (your global gpg signingkey);
# only the committer name/email change here.
#
# Examples — replace with your own:
# github|acme|Bogdan Grozoiu|bogdan@acme.com
# azure|contoso|Bogdan Grozoiu|bogdan@contoso.com
# url|https://git.example.com/platform/**|Bogdan Grozoiu|bogdan@example.com
